<TITLE> PM to open curtailed Police Week Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 30 (bdnews24.com)The prime minister will launch the annual 'Police Week' by addressing senior police officials Tuesday at the International Conference Centre. A Police Headquarters press release issued Monday said the usual police parade, the police banquet and all other celebrations have been cancelled in the wake of the Peelkhana carnage. The press release said the curtailed Mar 31-Apr 2 programmes include a special conference, and a conference on crime control on the inaugural day. On April 1, the home minister's meeting with senior police officers, dinner with policemen, meeting at Police Officers' Mess, annual general meeting of the Police Service Association and a conference on the contemporary challenges faced by the police will take place. The April 2 activities will include the president addressing the senior police officers, the inspector general exchanging views with police officers and a conference of the retired and serving police officers
